    "Body": " LIMRA, LOMA, and our parent organization, LL Global, Inc., are the world's largest association of life insurance and financial services companies, which together represent more than 1,300 members across 64 countries, including most of the world's largest life insurance and retirement companies. Our mission is to advance the financial services industry by empowering our members with knowledge, insights, connections, and solutions. We are building a dream leadership team to further our mission, including a Leader for a newly-created team to lead and deliver on \u201cconnections and solutions.\u201d Who Are We? Recognized as the trusted source for industry knowledge, LIMRA and LOMA select only the most passionate and skilled professionals. Financial services companies look to LIMRA and LOMA for their research, training and development needs. As one of our leaders, you will reflect the core values that make us the world's leading industry trade association by delivering the best products and serving our members globally. Here, in a diverse environment, you will have the opportunity to help instill our company culture where we treat one another with respect and act with integrity in all we do. Serving our members for over 100 years, they turn to us first for: Research serving as a catalyst for new ideas, to better understand the industry, and plan for the future. Learning and development programs to assess, train and increase distribution productivity, as well as develop the next generation of corporate leaders. Connections with industry leaders and peers through study groups, committees, and conferences. And much more! In a rapidly changing marketplace, companies rely on us for our combination of industry insight, practical solutions, and unwavering commitment to their success. What Will You Be Doing? This position will be focused on bringing our members together and developing industry solutions that meet their needs. In addition to directly managing solution development, you will collaborate with the rest of the leadership team to set direction, objectives and long-term vision for industry solutions to be offered by the organization, in conjunction with an overall strategy for convening our members in any number of forums. Solutions: Your team will be responsible for defining the art-of-the-possible solutions that bring the value of our association to life. Working directly with members, you will lead all aspects of developing solutions that address a common issue, and bring it to market: strategy, planning, design, development, go-to-market execution, and member adoption. Convening: Members tell us that LIMRA and LOMA\u2019s ability to bring them together in committees, study groups, conferences, and working groups to discuss and address common challenges is one of the key benefits of membership. You will lead and work with the head of convening to continually enhance the value of coming together through defining best practices, establishing consistent approaches, and maintaining high standards for member experience when convening, Harnessing the power of convening has proven successful for the organization in developing solutions such as FraudShare and LIMRA Data Exchange Standards. You will be responsible for working with the owners of those products as well as our Blockchain partner to bring our offerings to the next level, expand their use, and fully realize their potential, while employing our collaborative model to identify new product ideas and develop additional industry solutions that are \u201cby our members, for our members.\u201d Who Are You? This is a role best suited to a proven leader adept at executing complex programs in highly collaborative environments through influence and creativity, with strong communication and product development skills. A deep commitment to listening and a bias toward action are key attributes for success. You should have an understanding of the insurance, retirement and workplace benefits market with a keen sense of evolving industry trends and resultant member needs. You must be ready, willing and able to lead a dynamic team that is passionate about bringing people together to have an optimal experience, identifying ways that our association can help our members address common issues across the financial services industry, and building solutions to those issues that are embraced by our members. Skills Solutioning and product development/management skills \u2013 ability to identify market trends and needs, analyze and understand the competitive landscape, translate member feedback into solutions that address customer problems, and to design, build and market compelling industry solutions Interpersonal and collaboration skills \u2013 ability to develop collaborative and trusted relationships with key stakeholders; ability to discover and identify issues and opportunities; ability to leverage business acumen to create a compelling business case and value proposition; ability to collaborate with all stakeholders in an open, respectful manner that keeps them motivated, engaged and committed Leadership skills \u2013 ability to develop compelling vision and to command attention and commitment from members, colleagues and direct reports Executive communication skills \u2013 ability to effectively communicate with all parties, including customer executives, internal cross-functional teams and partners; ability to listen to member feedback, identify most pressing issues, prioritize needs, and share across multiple channels within the organization; ability to \u201cconnect the dots\u201d on common issues among various member groups Presentation and messaging skills \u2013 ability to fully understand and effectively communicate the LIMRA/LOMA value proposition and industry solution messaging; ability to build executive presentations and effectively present them in front of internal and external audiences Time management skills \u2013 ability to handle multiple projects and prioritize under tight deadlines Experience and Education A minimum of 10-15 years of experience with an insurer, a software company, the insurance practice of a consulting firm, and/or a major insurance industry systems provider with strong preference given to candidates with a competitive intelligence and product development background Knowledge of insurance processes and solutions, specifically around platforms such as data analytics, APIs, microservices, and blockchain. Proficiency in the application of SaaS and PaaS, as well as being conversant in emerging and potentially disruptive technologies such as AI and IoT (for Life Insurance, Retirement, and/or Workplace Benefits). 7+ years experience leading a team, including as a leader to leaders, and a successful track record for managing, developing and inspiring your team. Prior P&L responsibility preferred BA/BS/MBA degree in a related field Attributes Visionary. Maintains a long-term, big-picture view of the business and identifies the long-term, future needs and opportunities. Comes up with and champions innovative, breakthrough ideas that create significant member value. Strategic. Synthesizes trends and identifies opportunities. Develops strategies that increase member value and contribute to LL Global\u2019s long-term success. Translates broad strategies into clear objectives and practical action plans. Member Centricity. Anticipates member\u2019s needs, understands what they value and identifies how LL Global can deliver on those. Keeps abreast of important industry trends. Collaborative. Successfully pulls together various stakeholder groups to achieve results ", 
